Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of completion time in a multi-access channel, which involves information theory and communication networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the Gaussian multi-access channel, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with multiple users transmitting data. The paper may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the transmission of data bits. Finally, the paper may be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it involves the concept of constrained rates.
